  "body": "In validator design spec, under [Attestations](https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/blob/dev/specs/validator/0_beacon-chain-validator.md#attestation-data). To include the following block roots in attestation we do:\r\n\r\n**Epoch boundary root**: `get_block_root(state, get_epoch_start_slot(slot_to_epoch(head.slot)))`\r\n**Justified block root**: `get_block_root(state, justified_epoch)`\r\n\r\nThere's a few special cases that the spec did not mention:\r\n1.) For genesis slot: what do attesters put for epoch boundary root and justified block root:\r\n2.) Before the first block gets justified: what do attesters put for justified block root:\r\n3.) During epoch boundary slot: what do attesters put for epoch boundary root? the previous epoch boundary root? ",
